Happy Saturday night, friends! I introduce you to the Aperol Margarita. 👏🏻 This drink is a fusion of two of my favorite cocktails :: the Aperol Spritz & the Margarita. It’s simple to make and the color is 😍👌🏻. In my opinion, an extra splash of Aperol and extra squeeze of orange is best. 😋 A bit of Cointreau could also be added for sweetness. 

All you need is ::
• 1 orange
• 50ml blanco tequila
• 25ml Aperol
• 25ml lime juice
• salt optional 

Fill a margarita glass with ice and chill in the fridge until ready to serve. Combine tequila, Aperol and lime juice in a cocktail shaker filled with ice, and shake vigorously. 🧊  
Cut orange into wedges. Remove ice from the margarita glass and rub the rim of the glass with a wedge of orange until coated. Dip the rim into salt, if desired, until the edges are lightly coated.   Strain the cocktail into the margarita glass filled with ice. Garnish with an orange wedge to serve. 🍊 

Add an extra splash of Aperol to taste! Cheers! 🍹

Happy Cinco de Mayo, friends! 🌮🥑💃🏼 Tonight’s a perfect excuse to try a new drink recipe. Here’s my “go-to” Paloma, which is like a grapefruit margarita! 🍹This has become the drink I make most for lake/beach/pool days and is what my friends request most when I “bar-tend” at home hangouts! 👏🏻 It’s light, low-cal, refreshing + full of Vitamin C! 👌🏻

I always eye-ball my mixing, but here’s my best shot at transferring the recipe. 😉 Adapt to taste!

• 1 part silver tequila (@camarenatequila is my go-to)
• 1 part pink grapefruit juice (love Simply Grapefruit, too)
• 2 parts Grapefruit @bublywater or @lacroixwater. Grapefruit @fevertreemixers can be challenging to find but is amazing in this recipe!! 
• Add agave to taste. Don’t skimp as agave helps pull out the flavor, too!

Shake/stir and pour over ice. Garnish with a fresh grapefruit slice and enjoy! 😋

This recipe can also be made easily in a large pitcher for serving groups! 🙌🏻
